race.comment: AHELLBENDA (1) resumes and the betting will be key with the Litt-trained galloper. Has her first full preparation for the stable and has trialled twice at Warwick Farm. Has an awkward gate but is good enough at best and McDougall is engaged and flies with the stable. RILEYCAT (3) made a strong late bid only to just miss when first-up last start over 1200m at Canberra. Will take a lot from that hitout. Placed to advantage and with Heywood going aboard, she will be hard to beat. FRISKEE FROG (2) pushed forward first-up beaten just 0.7 lengths over 1200m at Canberra. Drawn to enjoy a nice run on-speed just off the speed and is suitably placed. APPARATE (7) got closer off a wide gate at Canberra. Draws inside today with a 2kg claim and she has marginal claims.
